				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$d = \frac{k\lambda }{{\beta \cos \theta }}$$\end{document}where λ is the wavelength of the X-ray; β, FWHM width of the diffraction peak; θ, diffraction angle; and k, constant according to the Patterson28.

